// src/pages/universal-notes.astro
// Premium, native web text universal game notes configuration
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Soloverse Universal Game Notes</title>
    <style>
        :root {
            --bg-main: #0f1015;
            --bg-card: #171922;
            --text-primary: #ffffff;
            --text-secondary: #f3f4f6;
            --text-muted: #9ca3af;
            --text-divider: #2d313f;
            --color-accent: #3b82f6;
        }

        :root[data-theme="light"] {
            --bg-main: #f4f5f7;
            --bg-card: #ffffff;
            --text-primary: #111216;
            --text-secondary: #1f2937;
            --text-muted: #4b5563;
            --text-divider: #d1d5db;
            --color-accent: #1d4ed8;
        }

        body {
            font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif;
            background: var(--bg-main);
            color: var(--text-secondary);
            max-width: 750px;
            margin: 40px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            line-height: 1.7;
            transition: background 0.3s, color 0.3s;
        }
        .back-link {
            display: inline-block;
            color: var(--color-accent);
            text-decoration: none;
            font-weight: 700;
            margin-bottom: 25px;
            transition: color 0.15s;
        }
        .back-link:hover { color: var(--text-primary); }
        h1 { font-size: 2.3rem; color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: 5px; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: -0.03em; }
        .meta-tag { color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 40px; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; }
        
        /* Index Jump Matrix */
        .toc-box { 
            background: var(--bg-card); 
            border: 1px solid var(--text-divider); 
            padding: 24px; 
            border-radius: 12px; 
            margin: 30px 0; 
        }
        .toc-title { margin: 0 0 15px 0; color: var(--text-primary); font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 700; }
        .toc-list { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 10px; }
        .toc-link { color: var(--text-muted); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; transition: color 0.15s; }
        .toc-link:hover { color: var(--color-accent); }

        h2 { font-size: 1.5rem; color: var(--text-primary); margin-top: 50px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding-bottom: 8px; font-weight: 700; }
        h3 { font-size: 1.15rem; color: var(--text-primary); margin-top: 25px; font-weight: 700; }
        p { color: var(--text-secondary); margin: 16px 0; }
        
        /* Game Grid Contents styling */
        .expansion-grid { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 10px; margin: 20px 0; }
        .expansion-row { background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding: 12px 16px; border-radius: 8px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; gap: 15px; }
        .expansion-name { font-weight: 700; color: var(--text-primary); font-size: 0.95rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.02em; }
        .expansion-desc { font-weight: 500; color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.9rem; text-align: right; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <a href="/" class="back-link">📂 Return to Shelf Deck</a>

    <h1>SOLOVERSE [GAME NOTES]</h1>
    <div class="meta-tag">👥 Ages 7+, 3-10 Players • v1.0.1</div>

    <!-- INDEX JUMP MATRIX -->
    <div class="toc-box">
        <div class="toc-title">📋 Index Jump Matrix</div>
        <ul class="toc-list">
            <li><a href="#contents" class="toc-link">1. Complete Game Contents</a></li>
            <li><a href="#recommendations" class="toc-link">2. First Play Recommendations</a></li>
            <li><a href="#notes" class="toc-link">3. Important Notes</a></li>
            <li><a href="#definitions" class="toc-link">4. Turn Overview Definitions</a></li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- SECTION 1: GAME CONTENTS -->
    <h2 id="contents">1. Complete Game Contents</h2>
    <p>The total asset vault of the Soloverse tabletop landscape consists of the following baseline card divisions and functional modules:</p>
    
    <div class="expansion-grid">
        <div class="expansion-row">
            <span class="expansion-name">📦 Core Game</span>
            <span class="expansion-desc">[5 x Colours & Basic Chaos Cards]</span>
        </div>
        <div class="expansion-row">
            <span class="expansion-name">📦 Core Extension</span>
            <span class="expansion-desc">[1 x Colour & Moderate Chaos Cards]</span>
        </div>
        <div class="expansion-row">
            <span class="expansion-name">🚀 Core Booster Pack</span>
            <span class="expansion-desc">[Extra Copy of Most Core/Extension Chaos Cards]</span>
        </div>
        <div class="expansion-row">
            <span class="expansion-name">💥 Apocalypse Expansion</span>
            <span class="expansion-desc">[Chaos Draw +2 & +3]</span>
        </div>
        <div class="expansion-row">
            <span class="expansion-name">⚔️ Warzone Expansion</span>
            <span class="expansion-desc">[Chaos Draw +2/+3/+4 Specific Targeted]</span>
        </div>
        <div class="expansion-row">
            <span class="expansion-name">🌋 Devastation Expansion</span>
            <span class="expansion-desc">[Chaos Draw +5/+10]</span>
        </div>
        <div class="expansion-row">
            <span class="expansion-name">🎯 Catastrophe Expansion</span>
            <span class="expansion-desc">[Chaos Draw +5/+10 Specific Targeted]</span>
        </div>
        <div class="expansion-row">
            <span class="expansion-name">🛡️ Oblivion Expansion</span>
            <span class="expansion-desc">[Royal Knights]</span>
        </div>
        <div class="expansion-row">
            <span class="expansion-name">🌀 Singularity Expansion</span>
            <span class="expansion-desc">[SOL / OVE / RSE]</span>
        </div>
        <div class="expansion-row">
            <span class="expansion-name">⚠️ Crisis Expansion</span>
            <span class="expansion-desc">[Crisis]</span>
        </div>
        <div class="expansion-row">
            <span class="expansion-name">☣️ Contagion Expansion</span>
            <span class="expansion-desc">[Super Poison]</span>
        </div>
        <div class="expansion-row">
            <span class="expansion-name">🕊️ Containment Expansion</span>
            <span class="expansion-desc">[Super Mercy]</span>
        </div>
        <div class="expansion-row">
            <span class="expansion-name">🛡️ Contingency I Expansion</span>
            <span class="expansion-desc">[Discard Specific Colour]</span>
        </div>
        <div class="expansion-row">
            <span class="expansion-name">🎨 Coloured Extensions</span>
            <span class="expansion-desc">[7 x Colour Sets]</span>
        </div>
        <div class="expansion-row">
            <span class="expansion-name">🔄 Contingency II Expansion</span>
            <span class="expansion-desc">[Discard New Specific Colours]</span>
        </div>
        <div class="expansion-row">
            <span class="expansion-name">💀 Doomsday Expansion</span>
            <span class="expansion-desc">[Assassination & Regeneration]</span>
        </div>
        <div class="expansion-row">
            <span class="expansion-name">📜 Cataclysm Expansion</span>
            <span class="expansion-desc">[Ancient Stones]</span>
        </div>
        <div class="expansion-row">
            <span class="expansion-name">🏟️ Field Deck</span>
            <span class="expansion-desc">[Rule Changes]</span>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- SECTION 2: RECOMMENDATIONS -->
    <h2 id="recommendations">2. First Play Recommendations</h2>
    <p>To ensure a balanced and engaging transition into the Soloverse tactical system, we highly recommend advancing through the gameplay modules in the following tiered sequence:</p>
    
    <div style="background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding: 24px; border-radius: 12px; margin: 20px 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 20px;">
        
        <div style="display: flex; gap: 15px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding-bottom: 15px;">
            <span style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--color-accent);">01</span>
            <div>
                <strong style="color: var(--text-primary); display: block; margin-bottom: 4px;">Baseline Entry Stream</strong>
                <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--text-secondary);">For new players, utilize <strong>only</strong> the Core Game Cards. This provides the ultimate unweighted learning environment for your first play session.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div style="display: flex; gap: 15px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding-bottom: 15px;">
            <span style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--color-accent);">02</span>
            <div>
                <strong style="color: var(--text-primary); display: block; margin-bottom: 4px;">Graduated Extension Trial</strong>
                <p style="margin: 0 0 12px 0; font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--text-secondary);">While adding the complete Core Extension is not advised for absolute beginners, a limited collection of specific cards can be safely integrated if desired:</p>
                <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 20px; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-muted); display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px;">
                    <li><strong>All Orange Number &amp; Action Class Cards:</strong> Icons like <em>Discard Colour</em> can trigger text confusion if a physical colour node is missing from play. Add these in if formatting tracking becomes an issue.</li>
                    <li><strong>Streamlined Chaos Module Subset:</strong> Consider introducing the following lightweight cards: <em>Badge Collector [x2], Black Hole, Paradigm Shift, United We Fall, Vaccine</em>, and <em>White Hole</em>.</li>
                </ul>
                <div style="margin-top: 12px; background: var(--bg-main); padding: 10px 14px; border-radius: 6px; border-left: 3px solid var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 600;">
                    💡 NOTE: These dynamic Chaos elements are far simpler than most alternatives in the Core Extension stack, making them excellent entry points.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div style="display: flex; gap: 15px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding-bottom: 15px;">
            <span style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--color-accent);">03</span>
            <div>
                <strong style="color: var(--text-primary); display: block; margin-bottom: 4px;">Expansion Containment Rule</strong>
                <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--text-secondary);">Do not introduce any Optional Expansion Packs during your first few trial cycles. Keeping complex expansion layer modifiers frozen leaves the baseline engine clean while new players learn the core loop mechanics.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div style="display: flex; gap: 15px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding-bottom: 15px;">
            <span style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--color-accent);">04</span>
            <div>
                <strong style="color: var(--text-primary); display: block; margin-bottom: 4px;">Full Grid Deployment</strong>
                <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--text-secondary);">Once your participant circle has fully mastered the core rhythm, elevate your deck matrix complexity by deploying the complete Core Extension array layer.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div style="display: flex; gap: 15px;">
            <span style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--color-accent);">05</span>
            <div>
                <strong style="color: var(--text-primary); display: block; margin-bottom: 4px;">Advanced Catalyst Phase</strong>
                <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--text-secondary);">As system navigation becomes natural, push your tactical gameplay to its limit by introducing a couple of standalone expansions at once. The prime community recommendation to add first is the fan-favourite: <strong>Apocalypse Expansion</strong>.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

    </div>

    <!-- SECTION 3: IMPORTANT NOTES -->
    <h2 id="notes">3. Important Notes</h2>
    <p>Review these foundational operational parameters before executing advanced variant mechanics. These definitions dictate core resolution stacks during active card play:</p>

    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 20px; margin: 25px 0;">
        
        <!-- 1. DECK EXHAUSTION CRITICAL RULE -->
        <div style="background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.07); border: 1px solid rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.2); padding: 20px; border-radius: 12px; border-left: 4px solid #ef4444;">
            <strong style="color: #f87171; display: block; font-size: 1.05rem; margin-bottom: 6px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.03em;">⚠️ Critical: Deck Exhaustion Paradox</strong>
            <p style="margin: 0 0 10px 0; font-size: 0.95rem;"><strong>Never Re-Shuffle the Discards back into the main Deck.</strong> Doing so introduces an infinite gameplay state risk where a natural end condition cannot be reached. If the draw deck runs out of actionable cards, the game ends instantly and <strong>everyone loses!</strong></p>
            <div style="background: var(--bg-main); padding: 10px 14px; border-radius: 6px; font-size: 0.85rem; font-style: italic; color: var(--text-muted);">
                💡 STRATEGIC ADVICE: The <em>Recycle Chaos Card</em> from the Core Extension can modify this parameter by providing restorative resource options before a total wipe occurs.
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 2. DEAL VS DRAW PIPELINE -->
        <div style="background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding: 20px; border-radius: 12px;">
            <strong style="color: var(--text-primary); display: block; margin-bottom: 8px;">🔄 System Logic: Deal Effects vs. Draw Effects</strong>
            <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 20px; font-size: 0.95rem; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 10px;">
                <li><strong style="color: var(--color-accent);">Deal Effects:</strong> (Includes the initial table setup deal and layout flips). These elements bypass all active Trap Effects. If a Trap card is revealed during a deal sequence, temporarily pause, return it randomly to the deck, and continue processing.</li>
                <li><strong style="color: var(--text-primary);">Draw Effects:</strong> Standard mid-game play fetches follow the strict resolution line of any triggered Trap Effects.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- 3. OVERRIDE & DELAY CHRONOLOGY -->
        <div style="background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding: 20px; border-radius: 12px;">
            <strong style="color: var(--text-primary); display: block; margin-bottom: 6px;">⚡ Chronology Rule: Override &amp; Delay Priorities</strong>
            <p style="margin: 0 0 12px 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">Whenever distinct card effects trigger overlapping mechanics or cause execution delays, <strong>the last card deployed always takes absolute priority</strong> over the execution stack.</p>
            <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px; font-size: 0.88rem; background: var(--bg-main); padding: 12px; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);">
                <div>🔵 <strong>Stun vs. Vaccine:</strong> If a <em>Stun Chaos Card</em> is in play and a player responds with <em>Vaccine</em>, the Stun card is frozen and cannot deactivate or impact its target until the entire <em>Vaccine</em> resolution stack is fully clear.</div>
                <div>🔵 <strong>Skipped Round vs. Vaccine:</strong> If <em>Vaccine</em> is deployed and its owner's turn sequence is subsequently skipped, the <em>Vaccine</em> card cannot deactivate at the standard interval because its host user failed to achieve a valid playable turn block that round.</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 4. PLAYABLE TURN BOUNDARY -->
        <div style="background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding: 20px; border-radius: 12px;">
            <strong style="color: var(--text-primary); display: block; margin-bottom: 6px;">🕹️ Gameplay Boundary: Defining a "Playable Turn"</strong>
            <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">A <strong>Playable Turn</strong> describes an isolated action window where a user has full autonomy to select and play any valid card format from their personal hand layer. It <strong>does not</strong> describe an automated round sequence where a player is trapped resolving mandatory card effects (such as clearing a forced skip modifier or answering stacked draw components in kind).</p>
        </div>

        <!-- 5. GROUP DISCARD & TURN ORDER TIMING -->
        <div style="background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding: 20px; border-radius: 12px;">
            <strong style="color: var(--text-primary); display: block; margin-bottom: 6px;">⏱️ Resolution Order: Group Discard Operations</strong>
            <p style="margin: 0 0 12px 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">Strict turn progression order must be maintained during mass discard disruptions. This layout sequence determines winner verification boundaries:</p>
            <ul style="margin: 0 0 12px 0; padding-left: 20px; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-muted); display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 6px;">
                <li>Deploying a <em>Discard Chaos Card</em> when you only have Chaos units remaining assumes you are last to clear. Because players follow the circle structure, an opponent sitting ahead of you in turn order could discard their final assets first and claim victory before your block activates.</li>
                <li>When cards force a group discard of 1 or more units, following the player trail leaves the last player (usually the active user) with a tactical advantage to monitor table shifts and select the card that dictates subsequent gameplay directions.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- 6 & 7. TRAP CLASS INTEGRATION -->
        <div style="background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding: 20px; border-radius: 12px;">
            <strong style="color: var(--text-primary); display: block; margin-bottom: 8px;">🪤 Traps Stack Layer: Double-Sided Mechanics</strong>
            <ul style="margin: 0 0 12px 0; padding-left: 20px; font-size: 0.95rem; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px;">
                <li><strong>Dual-Sided Orientation:</strong> All Trap Class components appear face-up when shuffled inside the main deck block. When drawn, extract the trap card instantly and fulfill its criteria.</li>
                <li><strong>Resolution &amp; Re-Entry:</strong> Once all trap conditions are fully resolved, reshuffle the trap back into the main deck. If triggered while dealing table assets, return them randomly to the deck immediately.</li>
                <li><strong>Immunity Status:</strong> Trap Class elements <strong>cannot be countered</strong> by standard modules unless explicitly written on an expansion rule sheet. Instant cards like <em>Mercy</em> resolve before removal, stopping subsequent traps from triggering.</li>
                <li><strong>Multiple Trap Triggers:</strong> If multiple traps emerge sequentially during draw passes, stack the latest card on top of the active chain. Resolve its criteria first, pass it to an isolated "used pile" upon finalization, and step backward down the trap hierarchy until the path is clear before reshuffling all traps into the core deck.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- 8. SECONDARY EFFECTS TIMING MATRIX -->
        <div style="background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding: 20px; border-radius: 12px;">
            <strong style="color: var(--text-primary); display: block; margin-bottom: 6px;">🎨 Component Architecture: Secondary Effect Icons</strong>
            <p style="margin: 0 0 12px 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">Cards carrying twin functional properties process data columns based on a priority system. Text definitions list behaviors in order of priority, but actions resolve chronologically:</p>
            <div style="background: var(--bg-main); padding: 14px; border-radius: 8px; font-size: 0.9rem; border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);">
                🚀 <strong>Case Study — Chaos Draw +4 Reverse:</strong>
                <p style="margin: 8px 0 0 0; font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--text-muted);">The <em>Draw +4</em> remains the primary tactical asset, but the <em>Reverse</em> icon initiates chronologically first. The direction of play changes instantly, and the previous participant must answer the primary draw modifier. Once that draw penalty clears, the next player acts based on the modified reverse parameters—meaning they can match it with any colored reverse layout, even if the primary card was assigned a blue designation.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 9. COUNTER CLASS LEVELING HIERARCHY -->
        <div style="background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding: 20px; border-radius: 12px;">
            <strong style="color: var(--text-primary); display: block; margin-bottom: 6px;">🛡️ Tactical Hierarchy: Counter Class Scaling Levels</strong>
            <p style="margin: 0 0 12px 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">Every Counter Class item carries an explicit system weight value (e.g., Level 1, Level 3). A target player can counter an active modifier back at its user <strong>only if their responding card level is equal to or higher</strong> than the incoming component:</p>
            
            <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px; font-size: 0.88rem; background: var(--bg-main); padding: 12px; border-radius: 8px; margin-bottom: 12px;">
                <div>🔹 <strong>Not Me [Lv3 Counter]</strong> — Can counter itself and can counter lower values like <em>Nou</em> [Lv2].</div>

    <!-- SECTION 4: DEFINITIONS -->
    <h2 id="definitions">4. Turn Overview Definitions</h2>
    <p style="font-style: italic; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 25px;">
        💡 NOTE: These baseline phase definitions dictate chronological operations during complex timing disputes. Use these step structures to resolve stacking conflicts at the table:
    </p>

    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 24px; margin: 25px 0;">
        
        <!-- PHASE 1: OPENING PHASE -->
        <div style="background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding: 24px; border-radius: 12px; position: relative; overflow: hidden;">
            <div style="position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 4px; height: 100%; background: #3b82f6;"></div>
            <span style="font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; tracking: 0.05em; color: #3b82f6; display: block; margin-bottom: 4px;">Phase Loop 01</span>
            <strong style="color: var(--text-primary); font-size: 1.25rem; display: block; margin-bottom: 6px;">🌅 Opening Phase</strong>
            <p style="margin: 0 0 16px 0; font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--text-secondary);"><strong>Temporal Window:</strong> Triggers immediately following the previous player's End Phase, running entirely <em>before</em> your personal main turn track actually initiates.</p>
            
            <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 12px; border-top: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding-top: 16px;">
                <div>
                    <strong style="color: var(--text-primary); font-size: 0.9rem; display: block; margin-bottom: 4px;">⛓️ Core Function A: Carry Over Effects</strong>
                    <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--text-muted);">Incoming payload data (such as stacked penalties from a <em>Draw +2</em> or <em>Chaos Draw +4</em>) bridges across turn boundaries and forces resolution within this window before you achieve autonomy.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <strong style="color: var(--text-primary); font-size: 0.9rem; display: block; margin-bottom: 4px;">⚡ Core Function B: Pre-Turn Initialisation</strong>
                    <p style="margin: 0 0 8px 0; font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--text-muted);">Specific cards that state <em>"Activate before you start a Playable Turn"</em> must execute completely inside this container. Your Main Phase will not unlock until these values are calculated.</p>
                    <div style="background: var(--bg-main); padding: 10px 14px; border-radius: 6px; font-size: 0.82rem; border-left: 3px solid #3b82f6; color: var(--text-secondary);">
                        📘 <strong>CASE STUDY — Jack's Knight (Oblivion Expansion):</strong> This Royal Knight class asset alters the layout of your upcoming loop right here, allowing you to deploy 2 active cards during your main step instead of the default 1.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- PHASE 2: MAIN PHASE -->
        <div style="background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding: 24px; border-radius: 12px; position: relative; overflow: hidden;">
            <div style="position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 4px; height: 100%; background: #10b981;"></div>
            <span style="font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; tracking: 0.05em; color: #10b981; display: block; margin-bottom: 4px;">Phase Loop 02</span>
            <strong style="color: var(--text-primary); font-size: 1.25rem; display: block; margin-bottom: 6px;">⚔️ Main Phase</strong>
            <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--text-secondary);"><strong>Temporal Window:</strong> Represents your active tactical gameplay window. This dictates the runtime window where you declare actions and execute the physical placement of your active card or card sets onto the discard table.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- PHASE 3: END PHASE -->
        <div style="background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding: 24px; border-radius: 12px; position: relative; overflow: hidden;">
            <div style="position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 4px; height: 100%; background: #f59e0b;"></div>
            <span style="font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; tracking: 0.05em; color: #f59e0b; display: block; margin-bottom: 4px;">Phase Loop 03</span>
            <strong style="color: var(--text-primary); font-size: 1.25rem; display: block; margin-bottom: 6px;">🌌 End Phase</strong>
            <p style="margin: 0 0 16px 0; font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--text-secondary);"><strong>Temporal Window:</strong> Represents the trailing terminal lock phase of your turn. This steps in directly between your active Main Phase actions and the next player's upcoming Opening Phase track.</p>
            
            <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 14px; border-top: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding-top: 16px; font-size: 0.9rem;">
                <div>
                    <strong style="color: var(--text-primary); display: block; margin-bottom: 4px;">🛠️ Step A: Effect Finalisation</strong>
                    <p style="margin: 0; color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.88rem;">The terminal wrapper of your active card play. For example, declaring your chosen continuous color after playing a Chaos asset locks in here, initiating the end phase.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <strong style="color: var(--text-primary); display: block; margin-bottom: 4px;">🏆 Step B: Victory Condition Verification Checks</strong>
                    <p style="margin: 0 0 8px 0; color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.88rem;">The system registers your hand payload capacity rules here to confirm win-state compliance:</p>
                    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 6px; font-size: 0.82rem; background: var(--bg-main); padding: 10px; border-radius: 6px; margin-bottom: 8px; border-left: 2px solid #f59e0b;">
                        <div>🔹 <strong>Baseline Check:</strong> System scans for an empty hand array. No cards remaining registers an immediate success state.</div>
                        <div>🔹 <strong>Draw Chain Exception:</strong> If your final card carries an active Draw penalty, your empty status is frozen. Play must trail around the circle in sequence until an opponent fails to match it and draws. Until that sub-routine completes, your win condition cannot finish executing.</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <strong style="color: var(--text-primary); display: block; margin-bottom: 4px;">💥 Step C: Tactical Interception Bounds</strong>
                    <p style="margin: 0 0 8px 0; color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.88rem;">Opponents can utilize specific counter modules within this micro-window to halt an imminent table victory.</p>
                    <div style="background: rgba(255, 242, 0, 0.05); padding: 12px; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 3px solid #fff200; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">
                        🎯 <strong>CASE STUDY — Anti-Fun Interception Counter:</strong> When you register an empty hand condition, an opponent can deploy <em>Anti-Fun</em> right inside your End Phase stack. This instantly drops 5 extra cards into your deck layer. Your victory script re-evaluates your hand, finds cards, cancels your win state, and forces your turn to close without achieving victory.
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <strong style="color: var(--text-primary); display: block; margin-bottom: 4px;">➡️ Step D: Payload Forwarding</strong>
                    <p style="margin: 0; color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.88rem;">Any lingering environmental card modifiers are bundled up and forwarded to the next player's opening phase vector.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

    </div>

    <!-- Silent local theme persistence tracking layout -->
    <script is:inline>
        const activeTheme = localStorage.getItem('soloverse-theme') || 'dark';
        document.documentElement.setAttribute('data-theme', activeTheme);
    </script>
</body>
</html>
